SUMMARY:Organic Reflections: Palms to Passion
DESCRIPTION:Resident Organist Larry Hershey will perform a concert\, “Palms to Passion” on the Hill Byrne/Christiansen Memorial Organ at First Reformed Church of Lancaster on Friday\, April 3 at 8 PM.  For the free 30 minute Good Friday concert\, Mr. Hershey has selected “Piece Heroique” by Cesar Frank\, a jazz work on “When I Survey the Wondrous Cross” by Joe Utterback\, the Bach/Virgil Fox arrangement of “Come\, Sweet Death”\, and “Father\, Into Thy Hands I Commend My Spirit” by Paul Sifler. \n\n\n\nThe First Friday “Organic Reflections” concert series is a gift to the community from First Reformed Church\, a center city congregation of the United Church of Christ.  Only 30 minutes in length\, the free concerts begin at 8 PM each First Friday for the convenience of those who wish to spend the early evening visiting downtown galleries before the concert.  Doors open at 7:30 pm.  All are welcome to hear 30 minutes of majestic music that will refresh your soul and inspire your spirit.  
URL:https://visitlancastercity.com/event/organic-reflections-palms-to-passion/
LOCATION:First Reformed Church\, 40 E Orange Street\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17602\, United States
CATEGORIES:First Friday,Free Events and Activites,Music and Dance
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visitlancastercity.com/wp-content/uploads/Memorial-Organ-2-Large.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="First Reformed Church":MAILTO:richardweinhold@yahoo.com
END:VEVENT
