SUMMARY:"March" Movie Night!  (Bumped to April 5th)
DESCRIPTION:Lancaster Freethought Society\nDue to scheduling and venue ava
 ilability\, March's movie night will be April 5th\, and is on Sunday inste
 ad of the usual Saturday!\n\nWe have a lot of great movies for this month!
  Options include:\n\nThe Act of Killing\n-Trailer- https://www.youtube.com
 /watch?v=6GiqYLrJBG0\n\nJesus Camp\n-Trailer- https://www.youtube.com/watc
 h?v=QBxATt-sP7Q\n\nDownfall\n-Trailer- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2Xi
 Y1ldtWVU\n\nBattle of Algiers\n-Trailer- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v
 hhoS3zOskE\n\nAnd many\, many more! Bring your own film selections and we 
 may decide to show them!\n\nAdmission is Free! Bring as many family member
 s and friends as you would like! Please RSVP! Discussion after the movie(s
 )\, hang out and share your thoughts!\n\nSome drinks and snacks will be pr
 ovided\, please do bring more to share!\nPizza will be ordered\, please do
  chip in if you partake in delivered food!\n\nSunday\, April 5th\, 6:00pm 
 - 10:00pm\nOther Room Theater\n715 N. Pine St.\nLancaster PA 17603\n\nWe c
 an delay starting the movie to give people time to arrive\, but no later t
 han 6:30pm\, please try to arrive before then if you do not want to miss a
 ny of the movie.\n\nPICTURED below is the main entrance\, the event space 
 is right up the stairs. On street parking should be available\, several pu
 blic parking lots such as behind CVS are within a 2 blocks walk along Harr
 isburg Pike.
