DESCRIPTION:Business & Career\, Tweens\, Teens\n\nRegistration will open a
 t 9:00 AM on Tuesday\, February 3\, 2026.  Registering for the first week 
 (March 3\, 2026) will hold your place for all six weeks of the workshop. T
 he Conestoga Toastmasters Club is conducting a free six-week workshop at t
 he library called Youth Leadership.The Youth Leadership Program consists o
 f six sessions helping those between the ages of 12 and 15 to develop thei
 r communication and leadership skills through practical experience. In the
  workshop\, young people will learn how to:Evaluate their own speaking abi
 lityPrepare and deliver speechesGive impromptu talksControl their voice\, 
 vocabulary\, and gesturesGive constructive feedback and moreConestoga Toas
 tmasters was founded in 1955 as a non-profit organization and are committe
 d to developing confident communicators and successful leaders who will po
 sitively influence the community.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Morgan Center A
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/youth-leadership-tweens-
 and-teens-toastmasters-151823
