SUMMARY:Revolution: The Music of the Beatles—A Symphonic Experience
DESCRIPTION:Experience The Beatles like never before as the LSO joins top vocalists and rock musicians to perform sweeping orchestral arrangements of more than 25 of the Fab Four’s top hits. Revolution immerses audiences in legendary songs like Ticket to Ride\, Penny Lane\, All You Need Is Love\, Get Back\, Here Comes the Sun\, and Hey Jude (and many more)—accompanied by stunning video\, animation\, and hundreds of rare and unseen photos from the archives of the band’s official fan magazine\, The Beatles Book Monthly. \n\n\n\nGrammy-winner Jeff Tyzik’s new arrangements\, transcribed and arranged from the original master recordings at Abbey Road\, bring The Beatles’ magic to life in this celebration of the band’s enduring legacy. \n\n\n\n\n    tickets
URL:https://figlancaster.com/event/revolution-the-music-of-the-beatles-a-symphonic-experience-2/
LOCATION:Lancaster County Convention Center\, 25 S Queen St\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17603\, United States
CATEGORIES:Arts & Entertainment
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://fig.guide/content/uploads/sites/3/2026/02/AprilWebsite.webp
ORGANIZER;CN="Lancaster Symphony Orchestra":MAILTO:info@lancastersymphony.org
END:VEVENT
