BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170439"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Kids' Garden Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260408T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260408T174500
UID:524baabc5dc380ab6fed281711ef7fd3@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Children\n\nSpring has sprung and it's time for so
 me garden fun!  Join us on our patio for our exciting garden time!  (Rain 
 or shine - if it's raining\, we'll be meeting indoors and limit our outsid
 e time.)  We'll read some stories\, do some crafts\, and of course\, get o
 ur hands in that soil and plant some seeds!  ***This week we'll be explori
 ng how seeds grow.  We'll plant some seeds and create a journal to track t
 he seed's growth.  Then we'll get our hands in our large planters and plan
 t some seeds.***We'll supply the seeds\, the tools\, and the planters - yo
 u supply your own gloves.  Plan on getting a little dirty.  This program i
 s for children ages 6 - 9 years old.  Registration will open at 9:00AM on 
 Wednesday\, March 25th for Manheim Township and East Lampeter residents an
 d on Wednesday\, April 1st for residents of other municipalities.Library P
 rogram Policies No Show – Patrons failing to cancel their registration
  for more than 2 library programs in a month will be restricted from regis
 tering for future programs for a period of one month’s time. Please canc
 el your registrations at least 2 hours prior to the start of the program t
 o allow those on the waiting list to be notified of their change in regist
 ration status. Late Arrivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior to t
 he start of the program to allow for parking and other circumstances. The 
 program will begin promptly at the designated time. At this time\, your sp
 ot will be forfeited to those on the wait list who will be granted entry. 
 If spots remain\, registrants may be allowed into the program. However\, r
 egistrants will not be permitted to enter the program 5 minutes past t
 he start time. Drop Off Program – This program is intended for childre
 n over the age of 6 years who can participate independently. Adult(s) must
  be present to check in child with youth services staff prior to program. 
 Adults will not be allowed in the event space.  *For children ages 6
 –7\, this is a drop-off program\; however\, a parent or caregiver must
  remain nearby and wait outside the program room for the duration of the
  program. Photography The Manheim Township Public Library Code of Conduct 
 Policy prohibits photographing or video recording individuals (including c
 hildren) without their consent (or in the case of a child\, the consent of
  a parent or guardian).
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Patio
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170439
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
