X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Body Doubling Session for Young Adults
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260409T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260409T200000
UID:4d30da58c5957cb9da043a02cec4ed8f@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Teens\, Adults\n\nStruggling to start or finish ta
 sks? Body doubling is a simple yet effective technique where people work a
 longside others in a calm\, structured environment to help improve focus a
 nd follow-through. In this facilitated session (particularly valuable to t
 hose with executive function challenges)\, participants ages 18-24 can bri
 ng homework\, job applications\, life admin tasks\, or creative projects a
 nd work quietly alongside others during guided focus periods. No pressure 
 to socialize\, share or communicate...just a supportive & quiet space to g
 et things done with others your age who are doing the same.To help us prov
 ide adequate supplies for the meeting\, please register to attend.
LOCATION:Lancaster\, LPL Meeting and Media Room
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/body-doubling-session-yo
 ung-adults-165845
