X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Church of the Apostles UCC": "https://apostlesucc.org/event/annual-garage-sale-day-1/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:apostlesucc
X-SOURCE:Church of the Apostles UCC
X-SOURCE-URL:https://apostlesucc.org/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T080000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T140000
DTSTAMP:20260403T224929
CREATED:20260204T173639Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T150843Z
UID:37876-1775808000-1775829600@apostlesucc.org
SUMMARY:Annual Garage Sale Day 1
DESCRIPTION:Searching for a massive\, budget-friendly yard sale in or near Lancaster? Look no further!\nJoin us at Church of the Apostles UCC for our annual garage sale held on the Friday and Saturday following Easter. Be prepared to shop early\, as there’s always a long line before doors open on Friday! \nThis years sale is set for April 10th from 8 AM – 2 PM & April 11th from 8 AM – 1 PM in and around Fellowship Hall. Our address is 1850 Marietta Avenue\, Lancaster PA. Be sure to follow signs for Fellowship Hall! \nAll are welcome to attend this fun-filled annual event. We have many low-priced items for you to browse through including clothing\, collectables\, home furnishings\, jewelry\, sports items\, tools\, toys and so much more! Food options include hotdogs\, sodas and baked goods on Friday and Saturday! Ample parking\, including accessible parking\, is available on both days. \nIf you are interested in donating items\, you can do so the week of the sale\, April 6th\, 7th\, & 8th\, from 9 AM – 9 PM\, or April 9th\, from 9 AM – 12 PM\, by the Fellowship Hall doors. For additional information\, please feel free to contact us at office@apostlesucc.org or by calling (717) 392-5718. \nDownload a Poster to Share!\nList of donatable items!
URL:https://apostlesucc.org/event/annual-garage-sale-day-1/
LOCATION:Church of the Apostles UCC\, 1850 Marietta Ave\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17603\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://apostlesucc.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Garage-Sale-2026-Flyer.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Fig Lancaster": "https://figlancaster.com/event/court-appointed-special-advocates-casa-community-awareness-breakfast/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:figlancaster
X-SOURCE:Fig Lancaster
X-SOURCE-URL:https://figlancaster.com/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T080000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T090000
DTSTAMP:20260403T224922
CREATED:20260305T143344Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260305T164811Z
UID:10014464-1775808000-1775811600@figlancaster.com
SUMMARY:Court Appointed Special Advocates (CASA) Community Awareness Breakfast
DESCRIPTION:Event Details\n\nJoin Court Appointed Special Advocates (CASA) for breakfast to learn how to participate in the critical advocacy work CASA provides for children who have experienced abuse and neglect and are placed in the foster care system.  \n\nHear from CASA staff and supporters about the crucial and life-changing impact CASA volunteers have on the lives of our community’s most vulnerable children.  \n\nThe Community Awareness Breakfast is open to anyone who wants to learn more about becoming a CASA volunteer\, donor\, or friend. Guests will be given the opportunity to make a contribution. \n\nThis event is free and open to the public\, but registration is required. Please feel free to bring a friend! Please register by March 30\, 2026.\n\nQuestions? Please contact raquel@casalancleb.org \n\n\nWho We Are \n\nCASA of Lancaster and Lebanon Counties recruits and trains citizen volunteers to advocate for the best interests of youth who have suffered abuse and neglect and are in the foster care system. \n\nWe have served over 1\,100 of Lancaster and Lebanon County’s most vulnerable children since our program began in 2009. \n\nOur mission is to provide a qualified and compassionate court-appointed volunteer advocate to every child who is abused and neglected\, to ensure the fundamental human right of having a safe\, nurturing\, and permanent home is met. \n\nTo learn more\, please visit www.casalancleb.org \n            \n        \n                \n                \n    Register Now
URL:https://figlancaster.com/event/court-appointed-special-advocates-casa-community-awareness-breakfast/
LOCATION:DoubleTree Resort\, 2400 Willow Street Pike\, Lancaster\, 17602
CATEGORIES:Community
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://fig.guide/content/uploads/sites/3/2026/03/Lancaster-breakfast-email.avif
ORGANIZER;CN="CASA of Lancaster and Lebanon Counties":MAILTO:margie@casalancleb.org
END:VEVENT
