SUMMARY:Rooting for You: A Community Plant Swap (Weather Conditional!)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260411T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260411T160000
UID:546024f3d329af638713d35038e31b73@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nReady to turn over a new leaf?
  Whether you’re a seasoned plant parent or just looking to grow your col
 lection\, join us on the patio for our community plant swap! Bring a healt
 hy plant or a rooted cutting to share and take home a new green friend!How
  it Works:Give One\, Get One: Bring a pest-free plant (potted or a cutting
  in a jar) to the swap table.Share the Knowledge: Feel free to bring care 
 instructions or ID tags for your plants so the new owner knows what they
 ’re getting!Branch Out: Meet fellow local gardeners and swap tips along 
 with your sprouts.Important Weather Note:Because we’ll be out on the pat
 io\, this event is weather conditional. In the event of heavy rain or extr
 eme temperatures\, the swap will be rescheduled. Please check the library 
 website or our social media page two hours before the event for any cancel
 lation updates!
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Patio
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/reserved-plant-swap-weat
 her-conditional-170089
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
