SUMMARY:The Reagan Years
DESCRIPTION:Saturday April 11th\, 2026\nDoors | 7:00 PM\nShow | 8:00 PM \nGeneral Admission Standing Room | $32.65 + Fees \n+$5 on All Day of Show Purchases\nPlease note this event is 21+ – Valid ID Required to Drink\nCome hungry! Snacks and light bites will be available at the canteen.\n————————————————–\nPresented by Mickey’s Black Box\n————————————————–\nBack to rock the house again\, The Reagan Years are the East Coast’s premier 1980’s tribute band! Having helped pioneer the 80’s tribute band concept since 1996\, The Reagan Years have become one of the Mid-Atlantic’s favorite tribute acts\, playing the greatest Pop\, Rock\, New Wave and Hair Metal hits of the Video Era.  \nIts a true celebration of the music you love (not the wig\, spandex or leg warmers)!  \nSee why The Reagan Years have been often imitated – but never replicated.  \nCheck out The Reagan Years here!\n————————————————–\n*Ticket Alert*  \nPurchase tickets through Mickeysblackbox.com ONLY. Any tickets purchased elsewhere will not be honored and we are not responsible for tickets purchased from 3rd parties. This includes Stubhub\, Ticketsaales.com\, or the host of other 3rd party sellers. Do not google the name of the band or Mickey’s to search for tickets. Go to Mickeysblackbox.com ONLY. Mickeysblackbox.com will never direct you anywhere but the official Ticketmaster event site. \n\nAll bags are subject are to search upon entry. Tickets are non-refundable\, save for instances in which performances are cancelled by Mickey’s Black Box. For more information about our venue or to make an ADA request\, please visit the FAQ page of our website: https://mickeysblackbox.com/faq/ or call our box office line at (717) 723 – 8463.
URL:https://mickeysblackbox.com/event/the-reagan-years/
LOCATION:Mickey’s Black Box\, 101 Rock Lititz Boulevard\, Lititz\, PA\, 17543\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mickeysblackbox.com/app/uploads/2026/01/TRY-6-Anthony-lines-Background-30YR-e1771481046275.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"American Music Theatre": "https://amtshows.com/show/alton-brown/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:amtshows
X-SOURCE:American Music Theatre
X-SOURCE-URL:https://amtshows.com/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260411T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260411T193000
DTSTAMP:20260403T224933
CREATED:20260126T143038Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260213T142559Z
UID:10001847-1775935800-1775935800@amtshows.com
SUMMARY:An Evening of Alton Brown
DESCRIPTION:Tickets: $64 $74 $84 \nVIP: Alton Brown VIP Experience: $200 \nIncludes: \n\nOne ticket for admission\nA special VIP experience one hour before show time.\nIt will include a brief Q&A session in the Theatre.\nA signed copy of Alton’s book.\n\n*There will be no individual photos or autographs\, however\, photos will be allowed during the experience.  Video is strictly prohibited. \n*If you purchase a VIP Experience\, AMT will notify you by email prior to the event to give you additional instructions. \nAlthough he’s keeping the details under wraps\, Brown has said that with An Evening of Alton Brown he’s “stirring up some twists on his greatest hits\,” and “spicing things up with new demonstrations\, music\, and slightly scaled-down mayhem.”  No matter what\, An Evening of Alton Brown will present Brown as you’ve never seen him — unless\, of course\, you’ve been invited to his house. \nBest known for creating and hosting groundbreaking television such as Good Eats\, Iron Chef America\, Cutthroat Kitchen\, and Food Network Star\, Brown has also built one of the most successful culinary touring franchises ever\, performing live in more than 300 cities for well over half a million fans. With An Evening of Alton Brown\, he strips away the spectacle in favor of connection\, spontaneity\, and storytelling\, delivering a show that is equal parts humor\, science\, food\, and heart. \nFor certain concerts\, audience members may prefer to stand or dance\, especially when encouraged by the artist to do so. Guest expectations differ\, so we simply ask all attendees to extend mutual respect toward one another and maintain awareness of those around them. Our staff will only intervene in matters of safety or when behavior is deemed unruly\, combative\, or disruptive to the overall performance.
URL:https://amtshows.com/show/alton-brown/
LOCATION:American Music Theatre\, 2425 Lincoln Hwy East\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17605\, United States
CATEGORIES:Celebrity Concerts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://amtshows.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/AB_Concessions-Events-and-News-for-Website-1920x1080-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
