SUMMARY:Etiquette Dinner Theater at The Log Cabin
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an interactive dining experience where a 4-course meal is paired with live interactive theater. As you dine\, actors humorously demonstrate proper (and improper) table manners through a playful story featuring rival etiquette experts and their eager students. With light audience participation and plenty of laughs\, the night blends refinement and fun into one unforgettable experience.\n\nThis event will be available on multiple dates but for a limited number of guests so book soon!\n\nDates: April 16\, 17\, 22\, 23\, 24\nLocation: The Log Cabin restaurant\, 11 Lehoy Forest Dr\, Leola\, PA 17540 \nTickets: EARLY BIRD $95 through March 15th | $120 after\n\nLearn more and purchase tickets at https://logcabin1933.com/etiquette-dinner/ \n            \n        \n                \n            \n                \n                \n    Buy Tickets
URL:https://figlancaster.com/event/etiquette-dinner-theater/
LOCATION:The Log Cabin Restaurant\, 11 Lehoy Forest Dr\, Leola\, 17540
CATEGORIES:Food & Drink
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://fig.guide/content/uploads/sites/3/2026/03/20260301_115220-scaled.avif
ORGANIZER;CN="The Log Cabin Restaurant":MAILTO:info@logcabin1933.com
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Fig Lancaster": "https://figlancaster.com/event/the-rise-and-fall-of-the-pennsylvania-railroad-lecture/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:figlancaster
X-SOURCE:Fig Lancaster
X-SOURCE-URL:https://figlancaster.com/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260416T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260416T200000
DTSTAMP:20260403T224922
CREATED:20260316T133925Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260316T133927Z
UID:10014502-1776362400-1776369600@figlancaster.com
SUMMARY:The Rise and Fall of the Pennsylvania Railroad Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Did you know the Pennsylvania Railroad—known as “The Pennsy”—was an industry leaderfor 122 years? \n\n\n\nJoin local historian and train enthusiast Jim Bennett for his presentation\, The Rise and Fallof the PA Railroad. This illustrated talk explores how the Pennsylvania Railroad fueledindustry and contributed to the growth and development of York and Lancaster Counties\,becoming the standard by which America’s railroads were measured. \n\n\n\nAttendees will learn about the railroad’s ambitious beginnings\, its rise to prominence\, andthe factors that ultimately led to its decline. Bennett\, a Lancaster County resident\, hasshared his engaging train talks with numerous local groups and brings a passion for railhistory to this in-depth look at one of America’s most influential corporations. \n\n\n\n\n    more info
URL:https://figlancaster.com/event/the-rise-and-fall-of-the-pennsylvania-railroad-lecture/
LOCATION:The Susquehanna National Heritage Area\, 1706 Long Level Road\, Wrightsville\, Pennsylvania\, United States
CATEGORIES:Education & Classes
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://fig.guide/content/uploads/sites/3/2026/03/smoker-lecture-2-scaled.avif
END:VEVENT
