UID:bd8d27491e1985379f008533195e4c25@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Toddlers\, Children\n\nJoin us for a cooperative m
 ovement program where we will use our imaginations while we play with a pa
 rachute! Stories and songs will be incorporated\, while we move about and 
 use our motor skills. A great activity for young children and their adults
  to come together and share an exciting and engaging play experience! (For
  safety reasons\, children must not be younger than 18 months or older tha
 n 3 years old with an adult\, adult involvement is required)Adults attendi
 ng with their child(ren) do NOT need to register. Please add any additiona
 l registrants to your registration if more than one child that will be par
 ticipating in the program.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, 
 April 8th for Manheim Township and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\,
  April 10th for residents of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Sho
 w – Patrons failing to cancel their registration for more than 2 library
  programs in a month will be restricted from registering for future progra
 ms for a period of one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at
  least 2 hours prior to the start of the program to allow for those on the
  waiting list to be notified of their change in registration status.Late A
 rrivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to 
 allow for parking and other circumstances. The program will begin promptly
  at the designated time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to tho
 se on the wait list who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registran
 ts may be allowed into the program. However\, registrants will not be perm
 itted to enter the program 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adul
 ts – This program is for adults and children to enjoy together. Please p
 lan to attend and be engaged with your child. Drop offs will not be permit
 ted.Cancellations- Please check your email prior to departing to verify th
 at the program has not been cancelled.Program Limits - Patrons are limited
  to one session of multiple session programs per week.
