X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/earth-day-extravaganza-143291"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Earth Day Extravaganza
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260418T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260418T140000
UID:1b423e29bbec51e07a10b78730ca922d@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Everyone\n\nCommunity members of all ages are invi
 ted to learn about environmental issues and solutions in a family-friendly
  atmosphere.Our host of eco-conscious contributors and entertainers will e
 ducate\, empower\, and inspire our community to welcome environmental-sust
 ainability practices into their daily lives.⚠ Please note\, Earth Day Ex
 travaganza is (mostly) an outdoor event\, but we will bring it inside in t
 he event of rain. This event will be held rain or shine!EARTH DAY EXTRAVAG
 ANZA SCHEDULE♻ 10AM-2PM: Children's Craft Tables♻ 10AM-2PM: Please Tou
 ch Table with Lancaster County Department of Parks & Recreation♻ 10AM-2P
 M: LPL Seed LibraryCheck out the launch of our NEW seed library\, offering
  free seeds to anyone in the community! Vegetable\, herb\, and flower seed
 s are available.♻ 10AM-2PM: Book Swap TableWant to get rid of your old b
 ooks sustainably? Come swap your pre-loved books for a new-to-you book fro
 m the Juliana Bookstore!♻ 10AM-2PM: Master GardenersLearn about native p
 lants and their ecological benefits\, how to select ones appropriate for y
 our landscape\, what to look for when buying them\, and other practical ti
 ps.♻ 10AM-2PM: Pennsylvania College of Art & DesignComplete a nature-rel
 ated craft with our friends from PCAD.♻ 10:30AM: Canticuentos: Celebremo
 s nuestra naturaleza¡Miss Vivi presenta Canticuentos! Disfruten en famili
 a de un tiempo especial celebrando la cultura hispana con cuentos\, cancio
 nes y mucho más. Este programa se ofrece completamente en español. Commu
 nity Room (library's 1st floor)♻ 11:30AM: Your Street Trees and the Urba
 n ForestTrees are critically important to our living in a healthy city\, n
 ot just in parks and yards\, but also along the streets and alleys. Learn 
 about the benefits of street trees from the City of Lancaster's Urban Fore
 ster. Community Room (library's 1st floor)♻ 12:30PM: Earth Day Storytime
 Spring into storytime with Miss Rachel during our annual celebration of Ea
 rth Day! Community Room (library's 1st floor)All events at the Earth Day E
 xtravaganza are free and open to the public.
LOCATION:Lancaster\, LPL Ewell Plaza
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/earth-day-extravaganza-1
 43291
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
