BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/reserved-farmland-preservation-program-164603"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Preserving the Heart of Lancaster: A Race Against Time
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260420T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260420T194500
UID:3f51eef99bfaac5d50bd95c7f8fa076a@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Discussion\, Presentation\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nLa
 ncaster County is famous for its rolling hills and rich agricultural herit
 age\, but the landscape is changing fast. We currently lose over 3\,000 ac
 res of farmland every year to development. With 70% of our county's fields
  still at risk\, the mission to protect our soil and water has never been 
 more urgent. Join Jeff Swinehart\, President and CEO of the Lancaster Farm
 land Trust to discover why farmland preservation is about much more than a
  pretty view. During this presentation\, Jeff will share his 24 years of e
 xpertise to explain how the preservation process works\, how it impacts ou
 r local groundwater and watersheds\, and what the future looks like for ou
 r community. Whether you are a curious neighbor\, a landowner exploring yo
 ur options\, or someone who simply wants to ensure Lancaster's agricultura
 l roots stay firmly planted\, this is your chance to see what is at stake.
  Come learn how we can work together to protect our home for generations t
 o come!
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Morgan Center B
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/reserved-farmland-preser
 vation-program-164603
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
