 oung children! This program features stories\, songs\, and hands-on activi
 ties tailored for preschool-aged kids. Each session focuses on building ea
 rly literacy\, motor skills\, and social interaction through playful explo
 ration.Perfect for ages 3–6 with an adult\, this program provides a welc
 oming and inclusive environment where kids can learn and grow together. Pa
 rents and caregivers are encouraged to participate and share in the joy of
  discovery with their little ones.Ms. Laura has over 20 years of preschool
  classroom experience bringing a wealth of knowledge in early childhood de
 velopment. Her approach focuses on creating a warm\, engaging\, and suppor
 tive environment where children can thrive.Adults attending with their chi
 ld(ren) do NOT need to register. Please add any additional registrants to 
 your registration if more than one child that will be participating in the
  program.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, April 8th for Man
 heim Township and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\, April 10th for r
 esidents of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Show – Patrons fai
 ling to cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in a mo
 nth will be restricted from registering for future programs for a period o
 f one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hours pr
 ior to the start of the program to allow for those on the waiting list to 
 be notified of their change in registration status.Late Arrivals – Pleas
 e arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for parking
  and other circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the designate
 d time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wait li
 st who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be allowed
  into the program. However\, registrants will not be permitted to enter th
 e program 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adults – This progr
 am is for adults and children to enjoy together. Please plan to attend and
  be engaged with your child. Drop offs will not be permitted.Cancellations
 - Please check your email prior to departing to verify that the program ha
 s not been cancelled.Program Limits - Patrons are limited to one session o
 f multiple session programs per week.Preschool Party Registration Requirem
 ents – All children who will be participating in the craft will need to 
 be registered as a participant to allow for adequate supplies.
