X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170440"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Kids' Garden Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T174500
UID:1cecf27596c4ed020e8e565ef4769268@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Children\n\nSpring has sprung and it's time for so
 me garden fun!  Join us on our patio for our exciting garden time!  (Rain 
 or shine - if it's raining\, we'll be meeting indoors and limit our outsid
 e time.)  We'll read some stories\, do some crafts\, and of course\, get o
 ur hands in that soil and plant some seeds!  ***This week we'll explore th
 e different parts of a plant -starting at a seed!  And we'll spend some ti
 me with our newly planted seeds in the pots.***We'll supply the seeds\, th
 e tools\, and the planters - you supply your own gloves.  Plan on getting 
 a little dirty.  This program is for children ages 6 - 9 years old.  Regis
 tration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, April 8th for Manheim Township 
 and East Lampeter residents and on Wednesday\, April 15th for residents of
  other municipalities.Library Program Policies No Show – Patrons faili
 ng to cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in a mont
 h will be restricted from registering for future programs for a period of 
 one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hours prio
 r to the start of the program to allow those on the waiting list to be not
 ified of their change in registration status. Late Arrivals – Please a
 rrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for parkin
 g and other circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the designat
 ed time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wait l
 ist who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be allowe
 d into the program. However\, registrants will not be permitted to ent
 er the program 5 minutes past the start time. Drop Off Program – This 
 program is intended for children over the age of 6 years who can participa
 te independently. Adult(s) must be present to check in child with youth se
 rvices staff prior to program. Adults will not be allowed in the event spa
 ce.  *For children ages 6–7\, this is a drop-off program\; however\,
  a parent or caregiver must remain nearby and wait outside the program r
 oom for the duration of the program. Photography The Manheim Township Pu
 blic Library Code of Conduct Policy prohibits photographing or video recor
 ding individuals (including children) without their consent (or in the cas
 e of a child\, the consent of a parent or guardian).
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Patio
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170440
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
