BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/lit-lovers-book-group-154143"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Lit Lovers Book Group
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260428T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260428T194500
UID:4587472370308b2a2ec27c3063ef58c7@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Book Club\, Adults\n\nLit Lovers is an eclectic reading group 
 with a primary focus on fiction\, while also exploring memoirs\, short sto
 ries\, biographies and autobiographies\, mysteries\, science fiction\, and
  select works of nonfiction. The group is known for its lively\, thoughtfu
 l discussions and makes a concerted effort to respect differing viewpoints
 . To keep conversations focused and meaningful\, social chatter\, gossip\,
  and romance novels are generally kept outside the allotted discussion tim
 e.Lit Lovers gravitate toward modern fiction distinguished by strong writi
 ng\, well-developed characters\, and compelling narratives. Common themes 
 include contemporary issues\, family conflict\, and the triumph of the hum
 an spirit\, with a healthy appreciation for humor. Members read for both p
 ersonal enrichment and enjoyment\, and the group frequently selects works 
 by international authors\, books set abroad\, or stories that explore mult
 icultural perspectives.For a list of this year's book selections\, click o
 n the photo to the left or pick up a bookmark at the library!
LOCATION:Milanof-Schock\, MJY Grissinger Board Room
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/lit-lovers-book-group-15
 4143
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
