BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Trust": "https://www.lancastertrust.com/community-events/mako-haejin-fujimura/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancastertrust
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Trust
X-SOURCE-URL:https://lancastertrust.com/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260501T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260501T203000
DTSTAMP:20260403T224927
CREATED:20260203T164243Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260203T164243Z
UID:3673-1777662000-1777667400@www.lancastertrust.com
SUMMARY:Mako & Haejin Fujimura
DESCRIPTION:Sponsored by The Open Discourse Coalition\, this special evening at The Trust welcomes back Makoto Fujimura\, accompanied by his wife\, Haejin Fujimura\, for a conversation centered on their forthcoming book\, “Beauty X Justice.” \nWe often imagine beauty and justice as opposites: one concerned with truth and fairness\, the other with aesthetics and adornment. What if they aren’t rivals at all? What if beauty and justice belong together\, moving in step to create lives\, communities\, and cultures marked by courage and abundance? \nIn this fireside-style conversation\, the Fujimuras will explore how beauty and justice can work hand in hand\, drawing from their shared life\, creative practice\, and public work. More than ideas alone\, this evening offers a close look at how their vision takes shape in the real world\, through art\, advocacy\, and cultural renewal. \nThe conversation will be guided by The Trust’s Founder & Curator\, Tom Becker\, beneath the Beaux Arts vaulted ceiling of The Trust Performing Arts Center in downtown Lancaster. \nBring your friends\, your curiosity\, and your questions. Seating is free with advanced registration. Space is limited\, so reserve your tickets early! \nReserve Your Tickets
URL:https://www.lancastertrust.com/community-events/mako-haejin-fujimura/
LOCATION:The Trust Performing Arts Center\, 37 N. Market St.\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17603\, United States
END:VEVENT
