UID:38055-1777732200-1777741200@apostlesucc.org
SUMMARY:Mocktails & Meaning™: "The Librarians" Documentary Screening
DESCRIPTION:Make plans for a special Mocktails & Meaning™ gathering on Saturday\, May 2nd at 2:30 PM in the Sanctuary as we host a screening of the documentary The Librarians. \nThis powerful film follows librarians across the United States who find themselves on the front lines of debates about censorship\, intellectual freedom\, and access to information. Through their stories\, the documentary explores what it means to defend the freedom to read in a time when books\, ideas\, and education are increasingly challenged in schools and communities. \nFollowing the screening\, we will hold a Q&A and open discussion\, creating space to reflect on the themes of the film and share thoughts together as a community. All are welcome for this thoughtful afternoon of film\, conversation\, and connection. \nRegister Now By Clicking Here
URL:https://apostlesucc.org/event/mocktails-meaning-the-librarians-documentary-screening/
LOCATION:Church of the Apostles UCC\, 1850 Marietta Ave\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17603\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://apostlesucc.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Mocktails-Meaning-Flyer-Banner-Landscape-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
