DESCRIPTION:Arts & Crafts\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nThe Blanketeers meet on th
 e 1st and 3rd Tuesday of each month. They get together to socialize and cr
 eate blankets of various kinds for Project Linus. Project Linus is a volun
 teer non-profit organization that created handmade blankets to give to chi
 ldren who are seriously ill\, traumatized or otherwise in need of new hand
 made blankets. Project Linus welcomes blankets in all styles\, including q
 uilts\, tied comforters\, fleece blankets\, crocheted and knitted afghans.
  No registration needed. For more information contact dguscott@lititzlibra
 ry.org or call 717-626-2255.
LOCATION:Lititz\, LTZ Community Room
