 ldren ages 0-12\, this program features engaging stories\, lively songs\, 
 and fun activities designed to spark a love of reading and learning. This 
 is a wonderful opportunity for families to bond\, build literacy skills\, 
 and create lasting memories together!Adults attending with their child(ren
 ) do NOT need to register. Please add any additional registrants to your r
 egistration if more than one child that will be participating in the progr
 am.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, April 29th for Manheim 
 Township and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\, May 1st for residents
  of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Show – Patrons failing to 
 cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in a month will
  be restricted from registering for future programs for a period of one mo
 nth’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hours prior to t
 he start of the program to allow for those on the waiting list to be notif
 ied of their change in registration status.Late Arrivals – Please arrive
  10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for parking and oth
 er circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the designated time. 
 At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wait list who w
 ill be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be allowed into th
 e program. However\, registrants will not be permitted to enter the progra
 m 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adults – This program is fo
 r adults and children to enjoy together. Please plan to attend and be enga
 ged with your child. Drop offs will not be permitted.Cancellations- Please
  check your email prior to departing to verify that the program has not be
 en cancelled.
