SUMMARY:Mystery Book Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260511T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260511T200000
UID:c397a810f8227325a2f19799935f1628@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Book Club\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nLove a good whodunit? Whether 
 you’re a fan of gritty noir\, cozy mysteries\, or psychological thriller
 s\, the Mystery Book Club is looking for new investigators to join our ran
 ks for the 2026 season.Join us on the 2nd Monday of each month from 7-8pm 
 as we dive into a new page-turner\, dissect the clues\, and see if anyone 
 managed to crack the case before the final chapter. It’s a year of suspe
 nse\, great conversation\, and maybe a few red herrings along the way.Regi
 stration is encouragedJanuary 12: The Puzzle Box by Danielle TrussoniFebru
 ary 9: The New Girl by Daniel SilvaMarch 9: The Stolen Queen by Fiona Davi
 sApril 13: Crime Scene by Jonathan & Jesse KellermanMay 11: Quiet Libraria
 n by Allen EskensJune 8: Footprints of God by Greg IilesJuly 13: The 7½ D
 eaths of Evelyn Hardcastle by Stuart TurtonAugust 10: Death & Judgement by
  Donna LeonSeptember 14: How to Solve Your Own Murder by Kristin PerrinOct
 ober 12: The Secret of Secrets by Dan BrownNovember 9: All the Colors of t
 he Dark by Christ WhitakerDecember 14: The Twelve Books of Christmas by Ka
 te Carlisle
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Morgan Center A
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/mystery-book-club-155470
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
