SUMMARY:Kids' Garden Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260513T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260513T174500
UID:2fa07940b128c1988170b3567c8c45bf@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Children\n\nSpring has sprung and it's time for so
 me garden fun!  Join us on our patio for our exciting garden time!  (Rain 
 or shine - if it's raining\, we'll be meeting indoors and limit our outsid
 e time.)  We'll read some stories\, do some crafts\, and of course\, get o
 ur hands in that soil and plant some seeds!  ***This week we'll be explori
 ng how to plant a rainbow and we'll be painting our very own pot.  We'll a
 lso get our hands dirty as we continue to take care of our plants in the p
 lanter.***We'll supply the seeds\, the tools\, and the planters - you supp
 ly your own gloves.  Plan on getting a little dirty.  This program is for 
 children ages 6 - 9 years old.  Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednes
 day\, April 29th for Manheim Township and East Lampeter residents and on W
 ednesday\, May 6th for residents of other municipalities.Library Program P
 olicies No Show – Patrons failing to cancel their registration for mor
 e than 2 library programs in a month will be restricted from registering f
 or future programs for a period of one month’s time. Please cancel your 
 registrations at least 2 hours prior to the start of the program to allow 
 those on the waiting list to be notified of their change in registration s
 tatus. Late Arrivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior to the start
  of the program to allow for parking and other circumstances. The program 
 will begin promptly at the designated time. At this time\, your spot will 
 be forfeited to those on the wait list who will be granted entry. If spots
  remain\, registrants may be allowed into the program. However\, registran
 ts will not be permitted to enter the program 5 minutes past the start
  time. Drop Off Program – This program is intended for children over t
 he age of 6 years who can participate independently. Adult(s) must be pres
 ent to check in child with youth services staff prior to program. Adults w
 ill not be allowed in the event space.  *For children ages 6–7\, thi
 s is a drop-off program\; however\, a parent or caregiver must remain ne
 arby and wait outside the program room for the duration of the program. 
 Photography The Manheim Township Public Library Code of Conduct Policy pro
 hibits photographing or video recording individuals (including children) w
 ithout their consent (or in the case of a child\, the consent of a parent 
 or guardian).
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Patio
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/kids-garden-club-170441
