DESCRIPTION:Book Club\, Health & Wellness\, Children\n\nAges 4-11\, regist
 ered patrons will be given 10 minute reading slots in order of signup.  Wa
 lk-ins may be accommodated if slots remain open after all registered reade
 rs have finished their turn. We thank each family for waiting outside the 
 Story Corner until your child's turn. Come read to a dog at Quarryville Li
 brary!  Lily and Carly will take turns coming to visit us. They love to he
 ar kids read and won't mind if you stumble on a word here or there.  Share
  a story you love with a furry friend\, or consider reading one of their f
 avorite books: Go\, Dog! Go! by PD EastmanNoodle and the No-Bones Day by J
 onathan GrazianoCan I Be Your Dog?  by Troy CummingsHarry the Dirty Dog by
  Gene ZionWhere's Spot? by Eric HillClifford the Big Red Dog by Norman Bri
 dwellSheep in a Jeep by Nancy ShawThe Landis family will be coming to our 
 library with one of their dogs (Lily and Carly) once per month and they ar
 e excited to listen to your stories. We thank them for volunteering to bri
 ng back this youth program!
LOCATION:Quarryville\, QVL Story Corner/Early Literacy Lab
