BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Church of the Apostles UCC": "https://apostlesucc.org/event/mocktails-meaning-behind-the-scenes-of-human-trafficking/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:apostlesucc
X-SOURCE:Church of the Apostles UCC
X-SOURCE-URL:https://apostlesucc.org/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260521T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260521T200000
DTSTAMP:20260403T224929
CREATED:20260127T165548Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260212T163704Z
UID:37833-1779388200-1779393600@apostlesucc.org
SUMMARY:Mocktails & Meaning™: Behind the Scenes of Human Trafficking
DESCRIPTION:Join us for our May 21\, 2026 Mocktails & Meaning™ gathering for a powerful and eye-opening conversation led by Brad Ortenzi\, Eastern USA Regional Director of ZOE International and Coordinator of the Berks and Lancaster County Human Trafficking Task Forces. Drawing on his experience as a former Ephrata Police Detective\, his work with federal and county child exploitation task forces\, and his international work combating trafficking in Thailand\, Brad will take us behind the scenes of human trafficking in Lancaster County. This session will explore how traffickers recruit and control victims\, the psychological realities of trauma bonding\, and how local task forces respond through both enforcement and prevention. Time will be set aside for questions and dialogue. We’ll be serving a Mai Tai Mocktail as we engage this important and impactful conversation. \nRegister By Clicking Here
URL:https://apostlesucc.org/event/mocktails-meaning-behind-the-scenes-of-human-trafficking/
LOCATION:Church of the Apostles UCC\, 1850 Marietta Ave\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17603\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://apostlesucc.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Mocktails-Meaning-Flyer-Banner-Landscape-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
