BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/parachute-play-148194"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Parachute Play
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260522T101500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260522T104500
UID:6e359be2cdda3ff93d0ca716c02d4e8d@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Toddlers\, Children\n\nJoin us for a cooperative m
 ovement program where we will use our imaginations while we play with a pa
 rachute! Stories and songs will be incorporated\, while we move about and 
 use our motor skills. A great activity for young children and their adults
  to come together and share an exciting and engaging play experience! (For
  safety reasons\, children must not be younger than 18 months or older tha
 n 3 years old with an adult\, adult involvement is required)Adults attendi
 ng with their child(ren) do NOT need to register. Please add any additiona
 l registrants to your registration if more than one child that will be par
 ticipating in the program.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, 
 May 13th for Manheim Township and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\, 
 May 15th for residents of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Show 
 – Patrons failing to cancel their registration for more than 2 library p
 rograms in a month will be restricted from registering for future programs
  for a period of one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations at l
 east 2 hours prior to the start of the program to allow for those on the w
 aiting list to be notified of their change in registration status.Late Arr
 ivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to al
 low for parking and other circumstances. The program will begin promptly a
 t the designated time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those
  on the wait list who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants
  may be allowed into the program. However\, registrants will not be permit
 ted to enter the program 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adults
  – This program is for adults and children to enjoy together. Please pla
 n to attend and be engaged with your child. Drop offs will not be permitte
 d.Cancellations- Please check your email prior to departing to verify that
  the program has not been cancelled.Program Limits - Patrons are limited t
 o one session of multiple session programs per week.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Lapp Story Silo
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/parachute-play-148194
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/dramatic-play-friday-147984"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Dramatic Play Friday
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260522T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260522T154500
UID:12a7ec3a6b2fa8bb4bb405f1bad75973@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Toddlers\, Children\n\nDrop-in program. No registration requir
 ed.Join us for a fun-filled adventure at the library! Children ages 2–7 
 are invited to explore their creativity and imagination through hands-on p
 retend play. This free program offers three exciting stations:Post Office:
  Dress up like a mail carrier\, sort mail\, and deliver letters and packag
 es just like a real mail carrier!Veterinary Office: Care for stuffed anima
 l patients as a vet\, complete with checkups and bandages.Diner: Serve up 
 delicious imaginary meals as a chef or take orders as a friendly server.Wi
 th plenty of props\, costumes\, and open-ended activities\, your child can
  explore new roles\, practice social skills\, and have a blast.  No regist
 ration is required—just drop in and play!Each family group must include 
 a responsible adult in the room at all times. This program is for children
  2 to 7 years old only! While other ages are welcome in the room\, we kind
 ly ask that the play area and toys remain reserved exclusively for the int
 ended age group to ensure a safe environment for young participants.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Lapp Story Silo
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/dramatic-play-friday-147
 984
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancaster Libraries": "https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/block-party-150155"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancaster_libraries
SUMMARY:Block Party!
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260522T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260522T143000
UID:d708d7d02403ff239bf5a965d0c17694@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, STEM\, Toddlers\, Children\n\nRegistration is requ
 ested\, drop ins are accommodated as space allows. Please join the waitlis
 t as we may schedule a second session if there is sufficient demand.Block 
 Party is an hour long free play session for preschoolers and their caregiv
 ers using our library's wooden block set\, people\, vehicles\, animals\, s
 carves\, photographs of buildings\, and other accompanying materials where
  preschoolers have the freedom to build and play as they wish.An adult sta
 ff member or volunteer is present to model open ended questions and other 
 supports for the adults participating.Young children learn best when they 
 are able to construct knowledge through meaningful play. With the material
 s provided children will build and experiment\, manipulate objects\, work 
 with others\, count and measure\, talk about what they are building and bu
 ilding vocabulary\; all activities that will help children to achieve the 
 Pennsylvania Learning Standards for early childhood in not only STEM areas
 \, but also in language and literacy development\, physical development an
 d social and emotional development.Block party has only three rules:1) Adu
 lt caregiver must be present in room2) No throwing blocks3) No knocking do
 wn anyone else's buildingThis program is sponsored by Reynolds & Shivery F
 uneral Home.
LOCATION:Quarryville\, QVL Story Corner/Early Literacy Lab
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/block-party-150155
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
