UID:9bda54e715eb2bc816d766c7b24a4bcf@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:STEM\, Toddlers\, Children\n\nDrop-in program. No registration
  required.Let your child’s imagination soar in this hands-on free play p
 rogram! Designed for kids ages 2-7\, this engaging session provides a crea
 tive and interactive environment where children can explore\, build\, and 
 learn through play. No registration is required.Using vibrant magnetic til
 es and a variety of manipulatives such as blocks\, gears\, and more\, chil
 dren will:Develop critical thinking and problem-solving skills.Enhance fin
 e motor abilities and hand-eye coordination.Foster collaboration and socia
 l interaction with peers.This open-ended program encourages creativity\, e
 xploration\, and discovery\, all while having fun! Whether constructing to
 wering structures\, creating intricate patterns\, or experimenting with ne
 w ideas\, kids will enjoy a safe\, educational experience.Each family grou
 p must include a responsible adult in the room at all times. This program 
 is for children 2 to 7 years old only! While other ages are welcome in the
  room\, we kindly ask that the play area and toys remain reserved exclusiv
 ely for the intended age group to ensure a safe environment for young part
 icipants.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Lapp Story Silo
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/wee-build-free-play-1479
 42
