X-SOURCE-URLS:{"American Music Theatre": "https://amtshows.com/show/jo-dee-messina-2026/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:amtshows
X-SOURCE:American Music Theatre
X-SOURCE-URL:https://amtshows.com/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260618T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260618T193000
DTSTAMP:20260403T224933
CREATED:20251103T153054Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260313T153442Z
UID:10001830-1781811000-1781811000@amtshows.com
SUMMARY:Jo Dee Messina with special guests The Bennett Hall Band
DESCRIPTION:Tickets: $49 $59 $69 $89\n \nWith powerhouse vocals\, undeniable stage presence\, and a string of chart-topping hits\, Jo Dee Messina remains one of country music’s most vibrant and beloved artists. From the moment she burst onto the scene with “Heads Carolina\, Tails California\,” Jo Dee has delivered anthems that defined an era and continue to connect with fans across generations. \nHer impressive career includes timeless favorites like “I’m Alright\,” “Bye-Bye\,” “Lesson in Leavin’\,” and “Stand Beside Me\,” along with multiple Platinum albums and CMA and ACM Award wins. Known for her high-energy shows and heartfelt storytelling\, Jo Dee’s live performances are a celebration of life\, love\, and resilience. \nThe Bennett Hall Band is a rising country trio made up of sisters Kat\, Presley\, and Josie Hall\, whose musical journey began at a young age and continues to captivate audiences across the country. Named in honor of their brother Bennett\, the band blends heartfelt storytelling\, tight sibling harmonies\, and impressive musicianship into an authentic and energetic live performance. \nKat and Presley began singing together as young children\, quickly developing a natural harmony that became the foundation of their sound. Kat soon added guitar and songwriting\, while Presley’s perfect pitch found a home on the keys. The youngest sister\, Josie\, brings vibrant energy on drums\, ukulele\, and percussion\, rounding out the trio’s dynamic stage presence. \nWith experience performing on renowned stages throughout Tennessee and beyond—including CMA Fest\, The Station Inn\, and the Franklin Main Street Festival—The Bennett Hall Band is quickly making its mark on the country music scene with talent\, heart\, and a sound well beyond their years. \nFor certain concerts\, audience members may prefer to stand or dance\, especially when encouraged by the artist to do so. Guest expectations differ\, so we simply ask all attendees to extend mutual respect toward one another and maintain awareness of those around them. Our staff will only intervene in matters of safety or when behavior is deemed unruly\, combative\, or disruptive to the overall performance.
URL:https://amtshows.com/show/jo-dee-messina-2026/
LOCATION:American Music Theatre\, 2425 Lincoln Hwy East\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17605\, United States
CATEGORIES:Celebrity Concerts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://amtshows.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/JDM_Concessions-Events-and-News-for-Website-1920x1080-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"American Music Theatre": "https://amtshows.com/show/lauren-daigle/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:amtshows
X-SOURCE:American Music Theatre
X-SOURCE-URL:https://amtshows.com/events/
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260619
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260620
DTSTAMP:20260403T224933
CREATED:20260309T143012Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260313T134910Z
UID:10001858-1781827200-1781913599@amtshows.com
SUMMARY:Lauren Daigle
DESCRIPTION:Tickets: $99 $139 $169 $229\nAMT Member Pre-Sale: Tuesday\, March 10 at 9:00 a.m.\nArtist Pre-Sale: Tuesday\, March 10\, at 10:00 a.m. through Thursday\, March 12 10:00 p.m.\nPublic On-Sale: Friday\, March 13 at 10:00 a.m. \nLAUREN DAIGLE VIP EXPERIENCE $259 \nOne Incredible Reserved Seated Ticket * \nMemories to Last a Lifetime \n\nPreshow Song Performance by Lauren Daigle\nInsider’s Perspective on the Stories Behind the Song\nQuestion and Answer (Q&A) Session with Lauren Daigle\n\nOn-Site VIP Perks \n\nVIP Priority Check-In & Separate VIP Entrance\nCrowd-Free VIP Merchandise Shopping Opportunity\n\nLauren Daigle VIP Merchandise \n\nSpecial VIP Tour Gift (Created Exclusively for Package Purchasers)\nCommemorative Lauren Daigle VIP Laminate\n\n*Venue seating configurations can vary market-by-market. \nLAUREN DAIGLE VIP UPGRADE (TICKET NOT INCLUDED) ** $49 \nMemories to Last a Lifetime \n\nPreshow Song Performance by Lauren Daigle\nInsider’s Perspective on the Stories Behind the Song\nQuestion and Answer (Q&A) Session with Lauren Daigle\n\nOn-Site VIP Perks \n\nVIP Priority Check-In & Separate VIP Entrance\nCrowd-Free VIP Merchandise Shopping Opportunity\n\nLauren Daigle VIP Merchandise \n\nCommemorative Lauren Daigle VIP Laminate\n\n** A ticket to the show is not included in the Lauren Daigle VIP Upgrade – a ticket must be purchased separately \nVIP PACKAGE DISCLAIMERS \n\nAll package purchasers will be contacted via e-mail a few days prior to the event date with additional program details. If you do not receive an e-mail\, please contact LaurenDaigleVIP@aegpresents.com\n\nAll sales are final. There are no refunds or exchanges under any circumstances. All packages and package contents are non-transferable. The artist\, show and venue reserve the right to cancel any order for any reason. All VIP merchandise will be distributed at the show; some exceptions may apply. VIP merchandise is not required for venue entry. Package purchases are restricted to U.S. & Canadian addresses only. All VIP programs and times may vary market-by-market and are subject to modification at any time for any reason. Information provided at the time of purchase (name\, address\, e-mail\, etc.) is the same information that will be utilized for individual contact requirements as applicable. The artist\, tour\, promoter\, ticketing company\, venue or any other affiliated parties are not responsible for outdated or inaccurate information provided by the consumer at the time of purchase. Commemorative VIP laminates are for commemorative purposes only. The VIP laminate does not gain or authorize access into the venue\, VIP or any backstage areas.\nLauren Daigle is a multi-GRAMMY®-winning\, chart-topping vocalist whose powerful\, soulful sound has captivated audiences around the globe. With more than a billion streams worldwide and sold-out tours spanning North America\, Europe\, Australia\, and Africa\, she has graced some of the world’s most iconic stages\, from Carnegie Hall and Red Rocks to Radio City Music Hall\, the New Orleans Jazz Fest\, and Lollapalooza. She has also performed on one of the world’s biggest stages\, singing “America the Beautiful” at the Super Bowl alongside Trombone Shorty. \nHer breakthrough album Look Up Child (2x platinum) debuted at No. 3 on the Billboard Top 200 and made history as Daigle became the first female artist to simultaneously land in the Top 10 of both the Pop and Christian album charts. The album’s 6x platinum hit single “You Say” became one of the longest-running No. 1 songs in Billboard chart history. \nDaigle’s GRAMMY®-nominated self-titled album features standout tracks including “Thank God I Do\,” “These Are the Days\,” and “Be Okay\,” and fueled her wildly successful Kaleidoscope Tour and Kaleidoscope Nights\, which played to packed arenas and was extended by popular demand. Beyond the music\, Daigle is known for her commitment to giving back through her nonprofit\, The Price Fund\, which supports organizations focused on music education\, hunger relief\, and care for the elderly—making her impact felt both on and off the stage. \nFor certain concerts\, audience members may prefer to stand or dance\, especially when encouraged by the artist to do so. Guest expectations differ\, so we simply ask all attendees to extend mutual respect toward one another and maintain awareness of those around them. Our staff will only intervene in matters of safety or when behavior is deemed unruly\, combative\, or disruptive to the overall performance. \n 
URL:https://amtshows.com/show/lauren-daigle/
LOCATION:American Music Theatre\, 2425 Lincoln Hwy East\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17605\, United States
CATEGORIES:Celebrity Concerts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://amtshows.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/LD_Concessions-Events-and-News-for-Website-1920x1080-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
